latestPosts.caption:
Hello, A little intro post ♡ 

My name is Sophie (Heaven for life, married into it, Sophie Long for work!) 

I met Mr Heaven in a local nightclub 'my sister fancies you' was how it all started 18 years ago! 

I am a hand embroiderer - quite a niche job I know, but one I absolutely love. I did an apprenticeship in hand embroidery. 

My biggest claim to fame is that I worked on Kate Middleton's wedding dress! 

I have written two Embroidery books before I had children. 

I have two children, Ivy and Otis, who are 16 months apart (no Otis wasn't a mistake) 

I love tea and cake (would happily never eat savoury again!) This would be my last meal, if I had to pick.

*Weird and wonderful* 

Ad @twist_museum -  London's home of illusions on Oxford Street is well worth a visit if you are looking for some family fun! 

Wander around the underground museum, full of colour and amazement. The family-friendly experience has over 80 interactive exhibits that you can't help but get involved in! I think you can see we loved it. 

10/10 from us!

*Drippy*

Ad - I've got a good one for you tonight...

'Mum, can I get some drippy sunglasses?' Otis aged 7!! 

You what?! Drippy? God, I feel old!! 

Thankfully with chatgpt (although often referred to incorrect as chatgbk - always thinking of food) - I discovered it means trendy/stylish - so incase your little ones have also been watching too much YouTube, you know now! 

Anyway, I think my new outfit it pretty Drippy... dont you? (Gosh, Ivy would be cringing, think I will leave that word for the cool kids!! 

Jacket and jeans both @newlook - I love my leopard print jeans so couldn't walk away from the jacket (thin so more of a shacket - in the sale atm, sized up to 12)

Barrel leg white jeans - the perfect length for a shortie! Inspired by @missionstyle_ and her love for white jeans

latestPosts.caption:
*VR Gaming  - you what?!* 
Ad - As summer time arrived, it looked like the rain did too! Having thankfully outgrown softplays and with a love of gaming, in steps @vrxtra.kingston in @thebentallcentre .  

I will be honest, I haven't gamed since I was about 11, with Mari on my Game boy. I had no idea what I had signed myself up to, but I knew the kids would love it. Fully expected myself to be useless! 

If, like me, you are unsure, it's a big gaming studio on the ground floor. You get fitted with a VR headset and briefed on the instructions - what buttons to press, etc. We did a basic escape mission, like a virtual escape room. (Suitable for 7 plus ) 

You work as a team to crack puzzles, or if, like me, you wander around, totally confused and letting the rest of the team down. (Sorry, guys). 

Verdict - they LOVED it. All 3 were gutted when our hour was up. I was still confused as to what I was supposed to have done (but dont tell anyone). 

There are seats so next time we go, I will be a spectator as it must be hilarious watching others play, the screens show you what the gamers see and you can hear all their convos! 

Have you tried out VR gaming?

latestPosts.caption:
*Pancake heaven*

Ad- We were lucky enough to be invited along to the new @wearefuwafuwa in @thebentallcentre Kingston, to try out their famous fluffy soufflé Japanese pancakes. 

It is safe to say, we all loved them, as you can see by Otis' hamster cheeks. It was too much to ask him to wait for a photo - he tucked straight in! 

He ate very single scrap and actually asked for some of ours!! Safe to say, we are massive Fuwa Fuwa fans and have already said we will pop back on our next Kingston trip. 

Otis had Biscoff, Matt had pistachio and Ivy had Summer fruits.  They also serve matcha and ice cream - perfect little treats after a shopping trip. 

Open Mon - Friday 11am - 8pm, Saturday 10am- 8pm and Sunday 11am - 6pm.

latestPosts.caption:
*Fresh strawberries*

With strawberry season here, do you want to know the best way to store them to keep them fresh?!

Place them in a glass jar, with a piece of kitchen roll in the bottom to absorb moisture - in an air-tight container. Then, place that in the fridge. Only wash when you are ready to eat them!

*Cool Mum*

90% of the time, Ivy calls me 'cringe'! 🤣

 But for a few hours today, apparently, I was a cool mum!! So, I am taking that!!

 I took Ivy and Otis to London today to visit @twist_museum . I will share more next week. We spotted  @popmartuk, and after chats with @whatmariewears, I knew we had to go in!! 

A mc ds to line our stomachs, a mc fluffy to pass time in the queue, and then a good 30 minutes of looking at every box, they twisted my arm, and we made some purchases. 

Now I am left thinking, do I need a labubu?

♡Co ord @zara current - 2nd wear in first few days of it arriving!

latestPosts.caption:
*London's prettiest ice cream*

I'm so happy that @therealfruiticecreamco is back in London this Summer!!

 After an amazing pop-up in @anthropologieeu during Chelsea in Bloom - where the ice creams were topped with edible flowers - perfection! @therealfruiticecreamco are now back at @oldspitalfieldsmarket for the whole of June! Thursdays to Sundays - Go go go! 

A combination of vanilla ice cream with frozen fruit, making the most delicious ice cream (whipped up in front of you) with a range of flavours and toppings, this is the BEST ice cream you will EVER eat!! Keep a look out for special edition flavours too!!

latestPosts.caption:
*Aye Aye Captain*
Ad - Don't let the Great British weather put you off - we may have got a little damp... but it was all smiles onboard!

Fun family time onboard @goboatldn, our 3rd trip and it never disappoints! We grabbed a picnic, picked up the kids life jackets, plus a map and jumped on. (Actually, I tell everyone to go slow and no jumping or fast movements, jic!) 🤣

With a 2 hour booking, from Kingston, you are able to get leisurely down to Hampton Court and back to Kingston - the most gorgeous route - even in the rain! Feel the freedom of being your own Captain, or just sit back and enjoy! 

Incase you book during rainy season (aka Summer time here), don't worry @goboatldn have you covered with some big umbrellas! The captain may need a friendly shipmate, or a waterproof coat (it's hard to hold an umbrella, navigate the water and steer!!)

1, 2, 3 or 4 hr boat hire available for up to 8 people (plus a dog if you like). Prices from £65 for one hour
